
[1]troy-weight

   TROY-WEIGHT, n. The weight by which gold and silver, jewels, &c. are
   weighed. In this weight, 20 grains = a scruple, 3 scruples = a dram, 8
   drams = an ounce, and 12 ounces = one pound.
